Blocks.childText: 5 THE LAND CELESTIAL. Words by FANNY CHURCH. From 66 Little Sower." J. H. ROSECRANS. 1. There is a land ce - les - tial, A world that's bright and fair; There flows the peaceful riv - er, Be - neath the tree of life, And o'er its ho - ly beau - - ty, Floats not a cloud of care There comes no wail of mourn-ing, Nor sound of bit - ter - strife. Chorus. Land of per - fect beau - ty, World SO bright and fair, When will an - gels call me, When shall I be there ? 2 There are the sweet-voiced angels, 3 They stand before the Father, Around the great white throne, The Lord of life and love; Who bow in willing homage He smiles upon his children, To him who rules alone. He welcomes them above. Death guards the mystic portals, And all in joyous singing, And gently one by one And peace for evermore, He leads in weary mortals, There in that far-off country. Whose earthly work is done, Upon that golden shore. Land of, etc. Land of, etc.
